RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 92. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 47000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING OR STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $20,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since September 15 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CLASS CLOWN chased briefly then went up to duel from outside, put away inner rival past the three-eighths pole, opened up when roused in the lane, grew a bit weary late but held safely. DIAMONDS DANZING settled off the inside, went three wide into the turn, angled five wide leaving the bend, showed late effort and whittle the gap on the winner while gaining the place. KO OLINA bumped with inner rival leaving the gate, stepped to the front then dueled inside CLASS CLOWN, could not keep pace with that rival with three furlongs left to run, churned on down the stretch and managed to hold the show. SHE'S BULLETPROOF tracked from inside, trailed two wide into the lane, angled out in the lane and kept on for a minor award. SHANGHAI SUNRISE chased three deep into and around the bend, came four wide into the stretch and lacked a bid. BROKEN CIRCLE stumbled and bumped at the start, stalked between rivals two to three wide on the turn and weakened down the lane. WISHTHEYALLCOULDBE stalked on the inside, shifted to the two path on the turn and also weakened. PALEO'S PRINCESS stumbled in the beginning, chased five then six wide and failed to menace.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CREATIVE WAY sped to the front from inside while under pressure, cleared on the backstretch, challenged again on the far turn, lost command at the top of the lane, fought back gamely and gained command nearing the eighth pole, then drew clear in the final sixteenth. PLAY CHICKEN pressed from outside early then chased up the backstretch, bid outside on the far turn, took over at the top of the lane, dueled with CREATIVE WAY down the lane and faltered late. DERECHO DANDY chased three wide off the pace early, went three deep on the far turn, bumped outer rival in upper stretch, came with a late run but needed to find more. TIZ TOK stalked two to three wide early, four deep on the second bend, bumped with DERECHO DANDY in upper stretch and finished evenly late. NOBLE UNION stalked on the inside then moved off the rail on the clubhouse turn, chased two wide into the lane and lacked the needed response. RELAXED ARTIST (IRE) hit the gate and came away slow, tucked inside at the back, made progress along the rail on the far turn but flattened down the lane. TOO MUCH INFO up close early in the four path, chased three wide on the far turn and weakened.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GEEZER broke in and bumped GRAZED, vied three deep between early then chased the top pair leaving the backstretch, rounded the bend three then four wide, launched a bid from outside with a furlong remaining, took over shortly after and held over SPIRITUAL ADVISOR in the final moments. SPIRITUAL ADVISOR vied four deep and between foes early then chased the dueling leaders into the turn, drifted out to bump rival at the three-eighths pole, came three wide into the lane, moved in and rallied inside the leaders in deep stretch but ran out of time. GRAZED bumped with the winner at the start, fought for the lead between rivals then dueled outside a rival into the turn, battled three wide into the lane, put away inner rival midstretch but was soon challenged by GEEZER at the eighth pole, relinquished the lead shortly after but stayed on to the wire. DISKO TRIBUTE vied six deep early then chased four deep into the turn, got bumped into outer rival at the three-eighths pole, came five wide into the stretch and finished evenly. ON THE WHIM raced up close seven deep then chased five deep leaving the backstretch, got bumped at the three-eighths pole, exited the bend six wide and lacked a rally. CRIBBAGE BOARD vied inside several rivals then dueled with GRAZED, fought two wide into the drive, stayed on to midstretch and weakened in the furlong grounds. MEESH vied four deep between rivals then ceded command and angled to the inside for the turn but failed to respond when called upon. STAY IN THE GAME trailed off the rail into the turn, moved out and came seven wide into the lane and was not a factor.

COOL PAPA G set the pace under pressure early, dueled outside HABEAS into and around the turn, could not keep pace with that rival in upper stretch and weakened in the late stages. RACE.FOOTNOTES: TOLEDO ROCKET broke a step slow and got bumped, stalked from inside, bid along the rail at the five-sixteenths pole, took over in upper stretch and drew clear late. KING ZOG broke in, chased three deep around the turn, came four wide into the lane, bid in upper stretch but got outkicked by the winner. UNUSUAL WIN was off slow and lost path at the start, chased wide early off the pace, rounded the bend five then six wide, came out at the top of the lane and was not a factor. PRINCE GRAYGRAY broke in, closest in pursuit early, chased between on the turn then got boxed in behind the leader entering the lane, then weakened in the stretch run.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: DEPARTURE broke out and bumped rival, took control early from inside, coaxed along on the far turn two then three wide into the stretch, started to open up before being roused midstretch and coasted in late. ZIMBA WARRIOR brushed from inside at the start, chased three wide around the first turn, two wide into the lane and bested the rest. TAISHAN bumped into rival leaving the gate, settled inside, trailed three wide into the lane, moved back inside and got up for third. SPEED GRAZY chased in the four path outside a rival on the clubhouse turn, went three wide into the second bend, steered out at the five-sixteenths pole, entered the lane five wide and got edged for the show honors. BRAVESTONE prominent early in the two path, closest in pursuit three then four wide on the far turn and faded down the lane. ALPINE THUNDER got bumped into outer rival at the start, stalked along the rail through both turns and tired in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Bayakoa S. - Grade3 LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 8 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 97. Stakes Purse 100000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. By subscription of $100 each, on or before December 7th 2023 closed with 13 or by supplementary nomination of $2,000 each by closing time of entries. With $1,000 to pass the entry box and an additional $1 ,000 to start, with $100,000 Guaranteed. The winner to receive $60,000, $20,000 to Second, $12,000 to Third, $6,000 to Fourth, $2,000 to Fifth. Weights: Three year olds 121 lbs. Older 124 lbs. Non-winners of a Graded race at a mile or over in 2023 allowed 3 lbs., of a Graded race at a mile or over in 2022-2023 allowed 5 lbs. A trophy will be presented to the owner the winner. Nominations close December 7th, 2023.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MIDNIGHT MEMORIES stalked from inside then moved into the two path, roused still two wide on the far turn, angled to the outside of DESERT DAWN past the three-sixteenths pole, drew alongside with a sixteenth remaining and inched away late. DESERT DAWN stalked in the three path outside a rival early, bid three deep on the far turn, dueled four wide into the lane, kicked clear in upper stretch, began to drift in and was put to left handed urging, remained clear at the eighth pole, challenged by MIDNIGHT MEMORIES with a sixteenth to go and yielded to the winner. TURNERLOOSE became rank chasing off the inside approaching the clubhouse turn then drifted out a bit around the bend, stalked up the backstretch, chased two, three then four wide on the far turn, moved out in the lane and gained the show. GANADORA prompted the pace from outside, moved up on even terms in the middle stages, inched ahead at the three furlong pole, fought inside DESERT DAWN three wide into the lane, relinquished the lead at the top of the stretch and weakened in the late stages. SMOOTHLIKEBUTTAH tucked inside at the back, moved off the rail and went three wide on the far turn, angled out at the top of the lane and failed to threaten. TROUVILLE coaxed along early near the back, got floated out to the four path by TURNERLOOSE on the first turn, chased in range four then five wide on the far turn but flattened down the lane. VIOLENT RUNNER took control early from inside while under pressure, came off the rail around the clubhouse turn and went three wide into the backstretch, headed by outer rival in the middle stages, lost command and failed to keep up with outer rival approaching the five-sixteenths pole and gave way in the drive.
